%N A394499 Starting at one corner of n X n grid of dots, the maximum number of edges that can be drawn without lifting the pencil or going over a previously drawn edge.
%F A394499 For n > 1, a(n) = 2*((n - 1)^2 + 1) - (n mod 2).
%F A394499 a(2n + 1) = A081585(n), n>0.
%F A394499 a(2n) = A108099(n).
%e A394499 In a 3 X 3 grid of dots, a maximum of nine edges can be drawn. Therefore, a(3) = 9.
%Y A394499 Cf. A081585, A108099, A002522.
%K A394499 nonn,easy,new
%O A394499 1,2
